The paper proposes an automated framework for analyzing privacy policies using deep learning. The use of language models and neural network classifiers suggests a strong focus on natural language processing (NLP), which is a key area of research in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to privacy and data protection, which are relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI), which is relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of neural networks and machine learning techniques suggests a focus on the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
